<p>Collecting includes seeking, locating, acquiring, organizing, cataloging=
, displaying and storing.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Gelber_S_M_1999,_p._12_4-6" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-=
Gelber_S_M_1999,_p._12-4"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Collecting is appealing to many people=
 due to their interest in a particular subject and a desire to categorize a=
nd make order out of complexity. Some collectors are generalists, accumulat=
ing items from countries of the world. Others focus on a subtopic within th=
eir area of interest, perhaps 19th century postage stamps, <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Milk_bottle" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Milk b=
ottle">milk bottle</a> labels from Sussex, or Mongolian harnesses and tack,=
 Firearms (both modern and vintage).
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Stamp_album_sleeve.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-desc=
ription"><img alt=3D"A photo album spread open to show a collection of stam=
ps." src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Stamp=
_album_sleeve.jpg/250px-Stamp_album_sleeve.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D=
"250" height=3D"177" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"1540" dat=
a-file-height=3D"1090"></a><figcaption>A <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Stamp_album" title=3D"Stamp album">stamp album</a> used in <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stamp_collecting" title=3D"Stamp collecti=
ng">stamp collecting</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>Collecting is an ancient hobby, with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Caesar_Augustus" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Caesar Augustus">Caes=
ar Augustus</a> being a collector of coins.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-12"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup> Sometimes collectors have turned their hobby into a business, bec=
oming commercial dealers that trade in the items being collected.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Observing">Observing</h3><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHobby&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: Observing"><span>edit</span=
></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>An alternative to collecting physical objects is to observe and collect =
records of events of a particular kind. Examples include <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Train_spotting" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Train=
 spotting">train spotting</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bir=
d-watching" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Bird-watching">bird-watching</a>=
, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aircraft_spotting" title=3D"Airc=
raft spotting">aircraft spotting</a>, and any other form of systematic reco=
rding a particular phenomenon. The recording form can be written, photograp=
hic, online, etc.
</p>
