<p><i>Making</i> and <i>tinkering</i> includes working on self-motivated pr=
ojects for fulfillment. These projects may be progressive, irregular tasks =
performed over a long period of time.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_1-3" class=3D"r=
eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-:1-1"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup> Making and tinkering hobbies include higher-end projects, such as =
building or restoring a car or building a computer from individual parts. F=
or computer savvy do-it-yourself hobbyists, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Computer_numerical_control" title=3D"Computer numerical control">=
CNC</a> (Computer Numerical Control) machining may also be popular. A CNC m=
achine can be assembled and programmed to make different parts from wood or=
 metal.
</p><p>Tinkering is 'dabbling' with the making process, often applied to th=
e hobby of tinkering with car repairs, and various kinds of restoration: of=
 furniture, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antique_car" title=3D"=
Antique car">antique cars</a>, etc. It also applies to household tinkering:=
 repairing a wall, laying a pathway, etc. Examples of Making and Tinkering =
hobbies include <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scale_model" title=
=3D"Scale model">Scale modeling</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Model_engineering" title=3D"Model engineering">model engineering</a>, <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_printing" title=3D"3D printing">3=
D printing</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dressmaker" title=
=3D"Dressmaker">dressmaking</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Cooking" title=3D"Cooking">cooking</a>.
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scale_model" title=3D"Scale=
 model">Scale modeling</a> is making a replica of a real-life object in a s=
maller scale and dates back to prehistoric times with small clay "dolls" an=
d other children's toys that have been found near known populated areas. So=
me of the earliest scale models of residences were found in <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cucuteni%E2%80%93Trypillia_culture" title=3D"Cucu=
teni=E2=80=93Trypillia culture">Cucuteni=E2=80=93Trypillia culture</a> in E=
astern Europe. These artifacts were dated to be around 3000=E2=80=936000 BC=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ModelingHistory_13-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-ModelingHistory-13"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> Similar models dating back to the same period were found in ancient Egypt=
, India, China and Mesopotamia archaeological sites.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Mod=
elingHistory_13-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Hobby#cite_note-ModelingHistory-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>At the turn of the Industrial Age and through the 1920s, some famili=
es could afford things such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rai=
l_transport_modelling" title=3D"Rail transport modelling">electric trains</=
a>, wind-up toys (typically boats or cars) and the increasingly valuable ti=
n toy soldiers. The current form of scale modeling became popular shortly a=
fter <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" title=3D"World =
War II">World War II</a>. Before 1946, children as well as adults were cont=
ent in carving and shaping wooden replicas from block wood kits, often depi=
cting enemy aircraft to help with identification in case of an invasion.<su=
p class=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowr=
ap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed=
" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"not common knowledge (=
October 2019)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p><p>With the advent of modern plastics, the amount of skill required to =
get the basic shape accurately shown for any given subject was lessened, ma=
king it easier for people of all ages to begin assembling replicas in varyi=
ng scales. Superheroes, aero planes, boats, cars, tanks, artillery, and eve=
n figures of soldiers became quite popular subjects to build, paint and dis=
play. Although almost any subject can be found in almost any scale, there a=
re common scales for such miniatures which remain constant today.
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_engineering" title=3D=
"Model engineering">Model engineering</a> refers to building functioning ma=
chinery in metal, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internal=
_combustion" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Internal combustion">internal c=
ombustion</a> motors and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Live_stea=
m" title=3D"Live steam">live steam</a> models or locomotives. This is a dem=
anding hobby that requires a multitude of large and expensive <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_tools" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"M=
achine tools">machine tools</a>, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Lathe" title=3D"Lathe">lathes</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Milling_machine" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Milling machine"=
>mills</a>. This hobby originated in the United Kingdom in the late 19th ce=
ntury, later spreading and flourishing in the mid-20th century. Due to the =
expense and space required, it is becoming rare.
</p>
<figure typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/F=
ile:Z_scale_miniature_railroad.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=
=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Z_scale_minia=
ture_railroad.jpg/500px-Z_scale_miniature_railroad.jpg" decoding=3D"async" =
width=3D"400" height=3D"151" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"5=
30" data-file-height=3D"200"></a><figcaption>A coffee-table sized <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rail_transport_modelling" title=3D"Rail t=
ransport modelling">model railroad</a></figcaption></figure>
<p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_printing" title=3D"3D printi=
ng">3D Printing</a> is a relatively new technology and already a major hobb=
y as the cost of printers has fallen sharply. It is a good example of how h=
obbyists quickly engage with new technologies, communicate with one another=
 and become producers related to their former hobby. <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/3D_modeling" title=3D"3D modeling">3D modeling</a> is th=
e process of making mathematical representations of three dimensional items=
 and is an aspect of 3D printing.
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dressmaker" title=3D"Dressm=
aker">Dressmaking</a> has been a major hobby up until the late 20th century=
, in order to make cheap clothes, but also as a creative design and craft c=
hallenge. It has been reduced by the low cost of manufactured clothes.
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cooking" title=3D"Cooking">=
Cooking</a> is for some people an interest, a hobby, a challenge and a sour=
ce of significant satisfaction. For many other people it is a job, a chore,=
 a duty, like cleaning. In the early 21st century the importance of cooking=
 as a hobby was demonstrated by the high popularity of competitive televisi=
on cooking programs.
</p>
