<p>Activity participation includes partaking in "non-competitive, rule-base=
d pursuits."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_1-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-:1-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Outdoor_pursuits" class=3D"=
mw-redirect" title=3D"Outdoor pursuits">Outdoor pursuits</a> are the group =
of activities which occur outdoors. These hobbies include gardening, <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hill_walking" class=3D"mw-redirect" titl=
e=3D"Hill walking">hill walking</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Hiking" title=3D"Hiking">hiking</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Backpacking_(wilderness)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Backpacking =
(wilderness)">backpacking</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyc=
ling" title=3D"Cycling">cycling</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Canoeing" title=3D"Canoeing">canoeing</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Climbing" title=3D"Climbing">climbing</a>, <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caving" title=3D"Caving">caving</a>, fishing, <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hunting" title=3D"Hunting">hunting</a>, t=
arget shooting (informal or formal), <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Wildlife_viewing" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Wildlife viewing">wildl=
ife viewing</a> (as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birdwatching" =
title=3D"Birdwatching">birdwatching</a>) and engaging in <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Water_sport_(recreation)" class=3D"mw-redirect" titl=
e=3D"Water sport (recreation)">watersports</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Winter_sport" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Winter sport"=
>snowsports</a>.
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size mw-halign-right" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Gardening.jpg" class=3D"mw-fi=
le-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/=
thumb/c/c3/Gardening.jpg/250px-Gardening.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"2=
50" height=3D"188" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"2304" data-=
file-height=3D"1728"></a><figcaption>Gardening</figcaption></figure>
<p>One large subset of outdoor pursuits is gardening. <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Residential_garden" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Resi=
dential garden">Residential gardening</a> most often takes place in or abou=
t one's own residence, in a space referred to as the garden. Although a gar=
den typically is located on the land near a residence, it may also be locat=
ed on a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roof_garden" title=3D"Roof=
 garden">roof</a>, in an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atrium_(a=
rchitecture)" title=3D"Atrium (architecture)">atrium</a>, on a <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balcony" title=3D"Balcony">balcony</a>, in a <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Windowbox_(filmmaking)" title=3D"Wi=
ndowbox (filmmaking)">windowbox</a>, or on a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Patio_garden" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Patio garden">patio=
</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vivarium" title=3D"Vivariu=
m">vivarium</a>.
</p><p>Gardening also takes place in non-residential green areas, such as p=
arks, public or semi-public gardens (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Botanical_garden" title=3D"Botanical garden">botanical gardens</a> or <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zoological_garden" class=3D"mw-redir=
ect" title=3D"Zoological garden">zoological gardens</a>), <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amusement_park" title=3D"Amusement park">amusement<=
/a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theme_park" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Theme park">theme parks</a>, along transportation corridor=
s, and around <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tourism" title=3D"To=
urism">tourist attractions</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Garden_hotels" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Garden hotels">hotels</a>. I=
n these situations, a staff of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gar=
dener" title=3D"Gardener">gardeners</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Groundskeeper" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Groundskeeper">groun=
dskeepers</a> maintains the gardens.
</p>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Indoor_garden.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-descripti=
on"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/I=
ndoor_garden.jpg/250px-Indoor_garden.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"250" =
height=3D"188" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"760" data-file-=
height=3D"570"></a><figcaption>A variety of flowers and vegetables in an in=
door garden</figcaption></figure>
<p>Indoor gardening is concerned with growing <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Houseplant" title=3D"Houseplant">houseplants</a> within a <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House" title=3D"House">residence</a> or=
 building, in a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conservatory_(gree=
nhouse)" title=3D"Conservatory (greenhouse)">conservatory</a>, or in a <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Greenhouse" title=3D"Greenhouse">green=
house</a>. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indoor_garden" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Indoor garden">Indoor gardens</a> are sometimes inco=
rporated into <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_conditioning" ti=
tle=3D"Air conditioning">air conditioning</a> or heating systems.
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Water_gardening" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Water gardening">Water gardening</a> is concerned with=
 growing plants that have adapted to pools and ponds, along with <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aquascaping" title=3D"Aquascaping">aqua-scap=
ing</a> in planted <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aquarium" title=
=3D"Aquarium">aquariums</a>. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bog" =
title=3D"Bog">Bog</a> gardens are also considered a type of water garden. A=
 simple water garden may consist solely of a tub containing the water and p=
lants.
</p><p>Container gardening is concerned with growing plants in containers t=
hat are placed above the ground.
</p>
