" width=3D"250" height=3D"344" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D=
"400" data-file-height=3D"550"></a><figcaption>An amateur <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magic_(illusion)" title=3D"Magic (illusion)">magici=
an</a> performing</figcaption></figure>
<p>Many hobbies involve performances by the hobbyist, such as <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Singing" title=3D"Singing">singing</a>, acting,=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juggling" title=3D"Juggling">jugg=
ling</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magic_(illusion)" title=
=3D"Magic (illusion)">magic</a>, dancing, playing a <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Musical_instrument" title=3D"Musical instrument">musical =
instrument</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martial_arts" titl=
e=3D"Martial arts">martial arts</a>, and other <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Performing_arts" title=3D"Performing arts">performing arts</a>=
.
</p><p>Some hobbies may result in an end product. Examples of this would be=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Woodworking" title=3D"Woodworking=
">woodworking</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Photography#Ama=
teur" title=3D"Photography">photography</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Moviemaking" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Moviemaking">moviema=
king</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jewellery_making" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Jewellery making">jewelry making</a>, software pr=
ojects such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Photoshopping" clas=
s=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Photoshopping">Photoshopping</a> and home music =
or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Video_production" title=3D"Vide=
o production">video production</a>, making <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Friendship_bracelets" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Friendship br=
acelets">bracelets</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Art" title=
=3D"Art">artistic projects</a> such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Drawing" title=3D"Drawing">drawing</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Painting" title=3D"Painting">painting</a>, <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cosplay" title=3D"Cosplay">cosplay</a> (design, creatio=
n, and wearing a costume based on an already existing creative property), c=
reating models out of card stock or paper =E2=80=93 called <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Papercraft" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Papercr=
aft">papercraft</a> (which includes <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Origami" title=3D"Origami">origami</a>), Many of these fall under the cat=
egory <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_arts" title=3D"Visual=
 arts">visual arts</a>.
</p><p>Writing is often taken up as a hobby by aspiring writers and usually=
 appears in the form of personal <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B=
log" title=3D"Blog">blog</a>, guest posting or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Fan_fiction" title=3D"Fan fiction">fan fiction</a> (literary a=
rt resulting in creation of written content based on already existing, lice=
nsed creative property under specified terms).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-14" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-14"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reading_(process)" class=3D=
"mw-redirect" title=3D"Reading (process)">Reading</a> books, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ebook" title=3D"Ebook">eBooks</a>, magazines, co=
mics, or newspapers, along with browsing the internet is a common hobby, an=
d one that can trace its origins back hundreds of years. A love of literatu=
re, later in life, may be sparked by an interest in reading <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Children%27s_literature" title=3D"Children's lite=
rature">children's literature</a> as a child. Many of these fall under the =
category <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literary_arts" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Literary arts">literary arts</a>.
</p><p>Knitting or crocheting is a calming and productive hobby. It allows =
for creativity while making cozy items like scarves, blankets, or hats. It'=
s easy on the joints and can be done at a leisurely pace, making it perfect=
 for staying engaged and creating thoughtful gifts.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Sports_and_games">Sports an=
d games</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DHobb=
y&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit section: Sports and gam=
es"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sport" title=3D"Spor=
t">Sport</a></div><link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-dat=
a:TemplateStyles:r1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigatio=
n-not-searchable">Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ga=
me" title=3D"Game">Game</a></div>
<p>Stebbins<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_1-5" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-:1-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> distinguishes an =
amateur sports person and a hobbyist by suggesting a hobbyist plays in less=
 formal sports, or games that are rule bound and have no professional equiv=
alent. While an amateur sports individual plays a sport with a professional=
 equivalent, such as football or tennis. Amateur sport may range from infor=
mal play to highly competitive practice, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Deck_tennis" title=3D"Deck tennis">deck tennis</a> or long d=
istance trekking.
</p><p>The Department for Culture, Media, and Support in England suggests t=
hat playing sports benefits physical and mental health. A positive relation=
ship appeared between engaging in sports and improving overall health.<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Hobby#cite_note-15"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Psychological_role">Psychol=
ogical role</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Hobby&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Psychologi=
cal role"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</sp=
an></span></div>
<p>During the 20th century, there was extensive research into the important=
 role that <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Play_(activity)" title=
=3D"Play (activity)">play</a> has in human development. While most evident =
in childhood, play continues throughout life for many adults in the form of=
 games, hobbies, and sport.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-16"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Moreov=
er, studies of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aging_and_society#S=
uccessful_ageing" title=3D"Aging and society">aging and society</a> support=
 the value of hobbies in healthy aging.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-17"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Significant_achievements">S=
ignificant achievements</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.=
php?title=3DHobby&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D12" title=3D"Edit section=
: Significant achievements"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>There have been many instances where hobbyists and amateurs have achieve=
d significant discoveries and developments. These are a small sample.
</p>
<ul><li>Amateur astronomers have explored the skies for centuries and there=
 is a long list of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amateur_astrono=
my#Notable_amateur_astronomers" title=3D"Amateur astronomy">Notable amateur=
 astronomers</a> who have made major discoveries. Amateur astronomers <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Hale_(astronomer)" title=3D"Alan H=
ale (astronomer)">Alan Hale</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Thomas_Bopp" title=3D"Thomas Bopp">Thomas Bopp</a> discovered the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comet_Hale%E2%80%93Bopp" title=3D"Comet H=
ale=E2=80=93Bopp">Comet Hale=E2=80=93Bopp</a> in 1995.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1=
8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_=
note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li>A substantial amount of early scientific research came from the amateur=
 activities of the wealthy, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Antoine_Lavoisier" title=3D"Antoine Lavoisier">Antoine Lavoisier</a>'s co=
ntributions to the science of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chem=
istry" title=3D"Chemistry">chemistry</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Benjamin_Franklin" title=3D"Benjamin Franklin">Benjamin Franklin=
</a>'s investigations into <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electri=
city" title=3D"Electricity">electricity</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-19"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-20" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobby#cite_note-20"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_model" class=3D"mw=
-redirect" title=3D"Open-source model">Open source</a> is a development mod=
el using open collaboration to cooperate on projects. It is most notable in=
 the development of software and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/O=
pen-source_software#Key_projects" title=3D"Open-source software">widely use=
d software</a>, which has been developed and maintained by large numbers of=
 people, including many home-based amateurs with high-level expertise.</li>
<li>While the general public was not aware of nature observation which was =
formally conducted as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field_resear=
ch" title=3D"Field research">field research</a>, during the 1930s, practiti=
oners of the hobby went on to become the <a href=3D"https://en.wiktionary.o=
rg/wiki/pioneer" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"wikt:pioneer">pioneers</a> of the=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conservation_movement" title=3D"C=
onservation movement">conservation movement</a> that flourished in the UK f=
rom 1965 onwards.</li></ul>
